LAYOUT FORMAT

.kryon files declare widget hierarchies with IDs for controllers.

Syntax:

    window "title" width height {
        layout_type param=value param=value {
            widget_type id "property value"
            widget_type id param=value
        }
    }

Example:

    window "Counter" 300 200 {
        column gap=10 padding=20 {
            label lbl_count "Count: 0" align="center"
            button btn_inc "+"
            button btn_dec "-"
        }
    }

Supported layouts:

    column          gap=10 padding=20 align="center"
    row             gap=10 padding=20 justify="space-between"
    grid            columns=2 rows=2 gap=10
    absolute        (manual positioning)

Widget syntax:

    # Simple text widget
    label id1 "Hello, World"

    # Button with ID
    button btn_submit "Submit"

    # With parameters
    textinput name placeholder="Enter name" width=200

    # Container with children
    column gap=10 {
        label "First:"
        textinput first
        label "Last:"
        textinput last
    }

Controller usage (Lua):

    local count = 0
    local lbl = kryon.widget("lbl_count")

    kryon.widget("btn_inc").on_click(function()
        count = count + 1
        lbl.text = "Count: " .. count
    end)

    kryon.run()

Property types:

    string          "text value"
    integer         42
    boolean         0 or 1
    rect            "x y w h"
    enum            "start" | "center" | "end" | "stretch"

Direct 9P usage (no layout file):

    echo "create_window" > /mnt/kryon/ctl
    echo "My App" > /mnt/kryon/windows/1/title
    echo "create_widget 1 label 0" > /mnt/kryon/ctl
    echo "Hello" > /mnt/kryon/windows/1/widgets/1/text
